<section class="block-section story">
  <span class="section-tag">📖 Story</span>
  <h2>Why this block matters</h2>
  <p class="sub">Who gets displaced when a neighbourhood intensifies? Planning often skips this question.</p>
  <p>Optimisation tends to reward the plan that scores well on housing, access, and resilience, and to ignore the residents who lose their homes when a neighbourhood intensifies. This block centres the perspective planning often leaves out: informal settlements, affordability, and displacement. It is the direct parallel to Unit 5's stakeholder work, carried into the built environment. A redesign that raises every objective score while quietly clearing the people already living there has not solved the problem, it has moved it. Your plan has to face that honestly, the way you faced competing stakeholders in Unit 5.</p>
  <p class="sub" style="color: var(--muted);">Full block content lands in the Unit 6 deep build.</p>
</section>

